On January 21, 2013, President Barack Obama proclaimed it as the National Day of Hope and Resolve. In his proclamation, he reflected on the progress made during his first term as president and expressed his commitment to preserving the fundamental freedoms and protections of all Americans. He emphasized the importance of unity and working together to meet the challenges of the future. The proclamation called upon all Americans to join together in courage, compassion, and purpose to fulfill the promises of the country's founding and strive for a more perfect Union.